{
  "doc_id": "58001",
  "text": "Service: It is the realization of the semantics of the need of a communication element, based on \"service concept\" presented by Vissers, where users communicate with each other through a \"Service Provider\", whose interface is accomplished by a \"Service Access Point\" (SAP) [CITATION_1] . In the Entity Title Model the \"entity\" is the \"user\" of the Vissers service model and the \"Service Layer\" is the \"Service Provider\". In the Entity Title Model the SAP is formalized with the use of ontology, which in this work was built in OWL.",
